Subject:      Re: breath rules
In-Reply-To:  <199507051457.KAA21757@blues.epas.utoronto.ca> from "Michael
              Boughn" at Jul 5, 95 10:57:13 am
 
Not only is "Projective Verse" a polemical piece; it was written in a
flash; and I remember Olson saying he was surprised at its
canonization. Worse was the dumb response of (often unsympathetic)
academics, who started talking about "Projectivist" poets, and the
"breath-line"; a highly instructive article was written a few years
ago by a U. of T. woman who showed that Williams's lines are not oral
lines but something to read AGAINST the breath, as a tight music.
