Maybe she meant something as straightforward as her poems:
something is poetry when it makes you think/see/feel differently. It
suprises.
 
Must a poem surprise? And what does that have to do with "newness"? Every
breath is new, even if the air isn't fresh.
 
A thought on poetry=ink on a page/is a drawing?: Draw in a breath.
 
Willa
