Date:         Sun, 9 Jul 1995 05:29:45 -0700
Reply-To:     UB Poetics discussion group <POETICS@UBVM.CC.BUFFALO.EDU>
Sender:       UB Poetics discussion group <POETICS@UBVM.CC.BUFFALO.EDU>
From:         Ron Silliman <rsillima@IX.NETCOM.COM>
Subject:      Re: Jesture
 
Rod, you wrote"
 
& Ron S. (if you're out there, what's the role of
>revision in N/O? or the alphabet generally-- do you not do it?)
 
 
_Force_was composed almost entirely via revision. Most of the rest of
the Alphabet uses it very sparingly (most finished manuscripts are
99.99 percent unrevised, but it seldom ever gets quite all the way to
100 percent--I find spelling errors or realize an inversion that would
do wonderful things to the prosody or discover I've forgotten a word).
As I recall, O had a little revision in it, but N almost none
whatsoever, given its methodology that anything went.
