Johns Hopkins has just reprinted _The Geographical History of America_ pb.
$14.95. The full title is _The Geographical History of America or the
Relation of Human Nature to the Human Mind_. As many know, this is the text
which  includes the line "I am I because my little dog knows me." Also Dalkey
Archive will be reprinting _The Making of Americans_ in the fall. I think
just a re-shoot of the Something Else edition, all those mistakes we know &
love will remain.
 
Also, let me encourage people to pick up Joan Retallack's _Afterrimages_
recently published by Wesleyan (pb. $12.95).
We need to send the right message when an established press does a _living_
"experimental" (the following should be bold)
writer.
 
Support independent booksellers.
Go to Barnes & Noble last, please.
 
--Rod Smith
