Subject:      Re: Ashbery's process
 
Jordan Davis wrote:
>Anybody know anything about Ashbery & revision? Or >Coolidge?
 
The recent Shoptaw book gets into his process (_On the Outside Looking Out:
John Ashbery's Poetry_ Harvard $24.00 pb geeze). Similar actually to what
Byrd was describing re Olson.
Apparently, he tends to cut more than rewrite, & when cutting doesn't work
he'll write "the same poem" over again. The body of Shoptaw's text contains
quite a bit of discussion of process. There's  also an appendix which
reprints early drafts of "A Wave."
 
Coolidge is another & very good question.
 
--Rod Smith
