Date: Tue, 20 Jun 95 08:46:58 BST
From: Scott Coombs <scoombs@ie.oracle.com>
To: jma5@columbia.edu
Subject: private press survey
------ cut here --------------------------------------------------------------
Purely out of curiosity, I have prepared a questionnaire for private presses.
The purpose of this questionnaire is to discover the nature and behaviour of
private presses as businesses. As an amateur printer, I am interested in how
those who charge for their wares go about doing it. I was inspired by an
article called "The Economics of Printing Limited Editions" which appeared in
"Fine Print" in 1987. If I get a reasonable sample, I may be able to
compile the information in some useful format.
 
Anyway, if anyone is interested in seeing the survey, mail me at
scoombs@ie.oracle.com (or scoombs@us.oracle.com, if the first doesn't work).
 
Note that this has nothing to do with Oracle Corporation.
 
Regards,
 
Scott Coombs
