Lindz writes:
". . .writng can come from two places; experience and the soul."
 
I tend to think the writing comes from any number of places, probably more
than two. Returning to the Ashbery process discussion for a minute. In the
_Code of Signals_ interview he has a useful statement-- "I'm interested in
the way experience filters through me." You could say Cage was interested in
the same thing, he just had a cleaner filter, maybe the cleanest.
 
