I teach a different course every semester that I teach, and always
put on books that I have never taught before, and always at least one
that I have not read. One of the best courses was one I gave in 20thC
stuff in Montreal years ago; it was ALL made of texts I didnt know,
and I let this be known when the course started, and I guess there
were some students who thought I was conning them. Started with
Joyce's _Exiles_ and went from there. We all learned a lot that term.
