Another interesting book on modern poetics (or at least poetic form,
the concrete manifestation of poetics) is Donald Wesling's *The New
Poetries*. Interestingly, he treats the whole run since 1798 (*Lyrical
Ballads*) as of a piece, rather than proposing differences organized
around "centuries".
 
